9-576x1024.jpeg 576w, https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/WhatsApp-Image-2024-11-30-at-00.04.19-169x300.jpeg 169w, https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/WhatsApp-Image-2024-11-30-at-00.04.19-253x450.jpeg 253w, https:\/\/dunetrektours.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/12\/WhatsApp-Image-2024-11-30-at-00.04.19.jpeg 642w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 576px) 100vw, 576px\" \/>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t<\/section>\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-0c6c973 e-flex e-con-boxed e-con e-parent\" data-id=\"0c6c973\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-e-type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_has_onepagescroll_dot&quot;:&quot;yes&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t\t<div class=\"e-con-inner\">\n\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-f2632e4 e-con-full e-flex e-con e-child\" data-id=\"f2632e4\" data-element_type=\"container\" data-e-type=\"container\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_has_onepagescroll_dot&quot;:&quot;yes&quot;}\">\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-element elementor-element-bf194e1 elementor-widget elementor-widget-text-editor\" data-id=\"bf194e1\" data-element_type=\"widget\" data-e-type=\"widget\" data-settings=\"{&quot;ekit_we_effect_on&quot;:&quot;none&quot;}\" data-widget_type=\"text-editor.default\">\n\t\t\t\t<div class=\"elementor-widget-container\">\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<p><\/p>\n<p><b><span style=\"color: var(--accent); font-size: 1.618em; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Itinerary<\/span><br><\/b><\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p><b>Day 1: Marrakech \u2013 Nkob \u2013 Handour<\/b><\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>Transfer to Nkob: Depart from Marrakech with a scenic drive through the High Atlas Mountains and the Draa Valley.<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>Begin the Trek: Arrive at the village of Handour, the starting point of your trek. Meet your guide and mule team.<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>Overnight Stay: Enjoy dinner and stay overnight in a traditional Berber guesthouse.<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>&#8212;<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p><b>Day 2: Handour \u2013 Amalou n\u2019Oughyoul \u2013 Bab n\u2019Ali<\/b><\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>Trail Highlights: Trek through rocky landscapes, verdant oases, and picturesque plateaus.<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>Bab n\u2019Ali: Arrive at the iconic twin peaks of Bab n\u2019Ali, a striking rock formation surrounded by dramatic cliffs.<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>Overnight Camp: Set up camp near Bab n\u2019Ali and enjoy dinner under the stars.<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>&#8212;<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p><b>Day 3: Bab n\u2019Ali \u2013 Assif n\u2019Igli<\/b><\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>Journey Through Gorges: Pass through the lush valleys and narrow gorges of the Saghro region.<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>Berber Villages: Encounter local Berber communities, learning about their culture and way of life.<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>Overnight Camp: Camp by the Assif n\u2019Igli river, surrounded by stunning natural beauty.<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>&#8212;<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p><b>Day 4: Assif n\u2019Igli \u2013 Kouaouch<\/b><\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>Summit Kouaouch: Ascend to the summit of Kouaouch, the highest point in Jebel Saghro at 2,592 meters.<\/p>\n<p>&nbsp;Enjoy panoramic views of the surrounding peaks and desert landscapes.<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>Descent: Begin your descent to a nearby plateau.<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>Overnight Camp: Camp on the plateau, enjoying a peaceful night in the wilderness.<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>&#8212;<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p><b>Day 5: Plateau \u2013 Ighazoun<\/b><\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>Explore Stunning Plateaus: Continue your trek through expansive plateaus and rocky terrains.<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>Traditional Lunch: Savor a delicious meal prepared by your trekking team.<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>Overnight Stay: Arrive at the village of Ighazoun for a restful evening in a Berber guesthouse.<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>&#8212;<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p><b>Day 6: Ighazoun \u2013 Nkob \u2013 Marrakech<\/b><\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>Return to Nkob: Trek back to Nkob, where your journey began.<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>Drive to Marrakech: Enjoy a scenic transfer back to Marrakech, reflecting on your incredible adventure.<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>&#8212;<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p><b>Highlights of the Trek<\/b><\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>Marvel at the volcanic peaks and dramatic rock formations of Jebel Saghro.<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>Summit Kouaouch for breathtaking views of the mountains and desert.<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>Immerse yourself in the culture of the Berber people, visiting remote villages along the way.<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>Camp under the stars and experience the tranquility of Morocco\u2019s wild landscapes.<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>Explore lush oases, deep gorges, and vast plateaus.<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>&#8212;<\/p>\n<p><\/p>\n<p>This 6-day trek through the Aiguilles du Jebel Saghro is a perfect blend of adventure, culture, and natural beauty, offering an unparalleled journey through one of&nbsp;<\/p>\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<\/div>\n\t\t\t\t<section class=\"elementor-section elementor-top-section elementor-element elementor-element-32ce220 elementor-section-stretched elementor-section-boxed elementor-section-height-default elementor-section-height-default\" data-id=\"32ce220\" data-element_type=\"section\" data-e-type=\"section\" data-settings=\"{&quot;shape_divider_bottom&quot;:&quot;mountains&quot;,&quot;background_slideshow_gallery&quot;:[{&quot;id&quot;:11036,&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https:\\\/\\\/enazzema.com\\\/wp-content\\\/uploads\\\/2024\\\/08\\\/il-vagabiondo-vfcIM4WVYQA-unsplash-scaled.jpg&quot;}],&quot;stretch_section&quot;:&quot;section-stretched&quot;,&quot;background_background&quot;:&quot;slideshow&quot;,&quot;background_slideshow_loop&quot;:&quot;yes&quot;,&quot;background_slideshow_slide_duration&quot;:5000,&quot;background_slideshow_slide_transition&quot;:&quot;fade&quot;,&quot;background_slideshow_transition_duration&quot;:500,&quot;ekit_has_onepagescroll_dot&quot;:&quo